    <subfield code="a">Susan W. Hayward sends a &quot;trifling contribution&quot; for the anti-slavery bazaar, with her apologies. Hayward recalls the pleasure of &quot;breathing a purely anti-slavery atmosphere&quot; last year and the inspiration derived from Mrs. Follen. Hayward is grateful also to Wendell Phillips and hopes to secure a [lecture?] appointment from him for this winter.</subfield>
